THE bail hearing of three men accused of killing ANC councillor Sbonelo Ntshangase and two others has been postponed to 6 February. Nhlakanipho Ntombela (30), Bongani Dlamini (38) and Andile Gamede appeared in the Piet Retief Magistrates Court, Mpumalanga, yesterday, 30 January. They were arrested after the three victims were shot early in January in Longhomes township in Mkhondo. ALSO READ:Two bust for the murder of ANC councillor! It’s alleged that the men entered a yard and fired multiple shots before fleeing. Dlamini told the court he couldn’t afford a private lawyer and requested a Legal Aid representative. Two months before his murder, Ntshangase made a Facebook live stream after the brutal shooting of ANC deputy chairman Muzi Manyathi (41), who was gunned down at a filling station. You must be SIGNED IN to comment! A few hours after the murder, Ntshangase wrote about his anger over the shooting on social media. He said if anything happened to him, his comrades or his family, everyone should know that former Mkhondo mayor Vusi Motha and current mayor Mthokozisi Simelane were responsible. Motha has been arrested and is facing a charge of possession of an unlicensed firearm.